  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT256-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">poruḷ vilakkappaṭṭa kiḻavaṉ celavaḻuṅkiyatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What dispenses with going by HIM who was attracted by
          wealth. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT256">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l>maṇivārn taṉṉa mākkoṭi yaṟukai</l>
          <l>piṇikāṉ meṉkompu piṇaiyoṭu mārnta</l>
          <l>māṉē ṟukaḷuṅ kāṉam piṉpaṭa</l>
          <l>viṉainalam paṭīi varutu mavvarait</l>
          <l>tāṅka lollumō pūṅkuḻai yōyeṉac</l>
          <l>collā muṉṉar nillā vāki</l>
          <l>nīrvilaṅ kaḻita lāṉā</l>
          <l>tērvilaṅ kiṉavāṟ ṟerivai kaṇṇē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l rend="indent">“We shall come when work has turned out well,</l>
          <l rend="indent">afterwards , through the forest where the stag bounces about</l>
          <l rend="indent2">who has become full along with the doe from the tender twigs</l>
          <l rend="indent8">with linking stalks </l>
          <l rend="indent5">of the Aṟukai, the big creepers as if dripping with jewels. </l>
          <l rend="indent">Is it possible to endure that much, o you with the flower earring?”</l>
          <l rend="indent2">[Even] before [that] was said – without standing [still],</l>
          <l>unending in desolation, for water to be transverse, </l>
          <l>they did hinder the chariot, the eyes of the woman.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
